      "title": "[NPR Health News] Here's how medication abortion works with just one drug",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=www.npr.org&amp;sz=128\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\nThe Supreme Court on Monday said that telemedicine access to the abortion drug mifepristone can stay — for at least a week. But as mifepristone faces court challenges, another drug that remains available is safe and effective at ending early pregnancy.",
