    {
      "id": "https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/05/260502233911.htm",
      "url": "https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/05/260502233911.htm",
      "title": "[ScienceDaily] Scientists just discovered what coffee is really doing to your gut and brain",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=www.sciencedaily.com&amp;sz=128\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\nCoffee doesn’t just energize—it actively reshapes the gut and mind. Researchers found that both caffeinated and decaf coffee altered gut bacteria in ways linked to better mood and lower stress. Decaf even improved learning and memory, while caffeine boosted focus and reduced anxiety. Together, they show coffee works through multiple pathways beyond just caffeine.",
